<topic id="zendesk-transformation-output">
  <title>DITA Map Zendesk Publishing</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Transformation Scenarios<indexterm>DITA Map to Zendesk</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>DITA Map to Zendesk transformation </indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_nbl_cgk_54b"><ph keyref="product"/> can publish DITA topics to XHTML output and upload
      them directly as articles to <xref href="https://www.zendesk.com/" format="html"
        scope="external">Zendesk Help Center</xref>:<ol id="ol_obl_cgk_54b">
        <li id="li_rbl_cgk_54b">Start <ph keyref="product"/> and open a <term>DITA map</term><ph
            product="author editor authorEclipse editorEclipse"> in the <xref
              href="dita-maps-manager.dita#dita-maps-manager"><uicontrol>DITA Maps
                Manager</uicontrol> view</xref></ph>.</li>
        <li id="li_sbl_cgk_54b">Click the <uicontrol><image id="image_d3c_lxq_vr"
              href="../img/TransformConfig16.png"/>Configure Transformation Scenario(s)</uicontrol>
          button.</li>
        <li id="li_tbl_cgk_54b">Create a new transformation scenario of type
            <uicontrol>DITA-OT</uicontrol> and choose the <uicontrol>Zendesk Help Center
            XHTML</uicontrol> transformation type. </li>
        <li id="li_ubl_cgk_54b">Go to <uicontrol>Parameters</uicontrol> tab and set the following parameters:<p>
            <dl id="dl_qyz_vny_1qb">
              <dlentry>
                <dt>Zendesk Host</dt>
                <dd>URL reference to the Zendesk Help Center, for
                    example:<codeph>https://your-domain.zendesk.com</codeph></dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry>
                <dt>Zendesk username</dt>
                <dd>Username for the account used to upload the content.</dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry>
                <dt>Zendesk API Token</dt>
                <dd>An API token generated in the Zendesk admin pages necessary for authentication
                  to the server: <xref
                    href="https://support.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/226022787-Generating-a-new-API-token-"
                    format="html" scope="external"/></dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry>
                <dt>Zendesk article category</dt>
                <dd>The name of the category in which the articles are uploaded. The category needs
                  to be created in the Zendesk admin pages:<xref
                    href="https://support.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/218222877-Organizing-knowledge-base-content-in-categories-and-sections#topic_hjs_tl4_kk"
                    format="html" scope="external"/></dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry>
                <dt>Zendesk article section</dt>
                <dd>The name of the section (inside the parent category) in which articles are
                  uploaded. The section needs to be reated in the Zendesk admin pages: <xref
                    href="https://support.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/218222877-Organizing-knowledge-base-content-in-categories-and-sections#topic_ysj_wtt_zz"
                    format="html" scope="external"/></dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry>
                <dt>Zendesk create article draft</dt>
                <dd>This setting controls if the articles should be published as draft
                  articles.</dd>
              </dlentry>
              <dlentry>
                <dt>Zendesk permission group name</dt>
                <dd>The name of the permission group under which the request to upload articles is
                  made: <xref
                    href="https://support.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/203661966-Creating-managing-and-using-groups"
                    format="html" scope="external"/></dd>
              </dlentry>
            </dl>
          </p></li>
        <li id="li_vbl_cgk_54b">Save the changes and transform. </li>
      </ol></p>
  </body>
</topic>
